defaultThe Equator Principles are a risk management framework, adopted by financial institutions, for determining, assessing and managing environm
defaultental and social risk in projects and is primarily intended to provide a minimum standard for due diligence to support responsible risk decision-making. The Equator Principles are closely aligned to the relevant International Finance Corporation (IFC) Perf
defaultormance Standards.
